Patch Set 1:

Why not using u32x4_is_all_zero() ?

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Why not using u32x4_is_all_zero() ?

Hi Damjan,
u32x4_zero_byte_mask() is heavy on Arm, so I made a wrapper to simplify the logic on Arm only.

On x86, u32x4_zero_byte_mask() is calling intrinsic _mm_movemask_epi8(), which u32x4_is_all_zero() is calling intrinsic _mm_testz_si128(). So using u32x4_is_all_zero() to replace u32x4_zero_byte_mask() to change the SIMD instruction used on x86.

To not affecting x86, I made a new wrapper instead of using u32x4_is_all_zero() directly.
